(8, 7, '2024-10-02', 'Study Abroad Opportunities: IGC Complete guide to studying abroad in 2024', 'study-abroad-opportunities:-igc-complete-guide-to-studying-abroad-in-2024', 'Many questions may arise to IGC: Impact Global Consultant while you are planning to study abroad.', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Many questions may arise to IGC:</span><span lang=\"EN\"><a href=\"https://igc.com.bd/\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;\"> </span></a><a href=\"https://igc.com.bd/\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #1155cc;\">Impact Global Consultant</span></a></span><u><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #1155cc;\"> </span></u><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">while you are planning to study abroad. Nevertheless, don&rsquo;t stress; here is a list to take you ahead and simplify your study abroad opportunities in 2024. So let&rsquo;s start &ndash;</span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"margin-top: 24.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 23.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">1. Why should you study in another country?</span></strong></h1>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">There are thousands of reasons studying abroad and advanced programs are becoming more popular for Bangladeshi students. However, most international students are likely to consist of getting a quality education, gaining exposure to the culture of another country (and typically the second language), getting a global outlook, and enhancing future job prospects.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">For some, the idea of leaving their home and going to a new place is daunting. However, studying abroad is an exciting experience that can lead to better career prospects and more excellent knowledge of how the world operates.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">The kind of experience you&rsquo;ll have during your stay abroad will depend on where you go. So make sure you select a location based on your interests and the academic standing of the country so that you can maintain an appropriate balance between work and play.</span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 4.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_84d9nshp5pm5\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 17.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">2. Where should I go to study?</span></strong></h2>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">The choice of where you would like to go to school isn&rsquo;t easy. Alongside your interests, you must consider practical considerations such as the costs of studying in that particular country (both cost of tuition and living expenses), your job possibilities (is there an employment market?), and your overall security and well-being.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Also, you should consider what kind of lifestyle you want to lead while studying. For example, do you prefer to be in a large city or a smaller university town? Do you desire art and culture right at your doorstep or top-of-the-line sporting facilities? Whatever your passions, make sure to connect them with your chosen study destination to have the best chance to enjoy your travels abroad.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">If you&rsquo;re having trouble making the right choice, then take a look at some of our most sought-after destinations, including the USA, the UK, Australia, Canada, Malaysia, China, and Germany, and click these links to browse our university rankings as well as a complete range of guides to the countries:</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_2sgc6uc7p9zk\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">3. How can I begin?</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">After you&rsquo;ve decided in your mind where you&rsquo;d like to go to school, You should begin to think about deciding on an academic program and a college in case you didn&rsquo;t yet. Research top universities using QSWorld University Rankings. Utilize subjects rankings to identify the best </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">universities for your particular field, and you can also look up the national rankings of the universities you&rsquo;ve chosen to study.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">It is then essential to look at the classes offered by the institutions you have on your list and research the area, lifestyle, admission requirements, and cost.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Once you&rsquo;ve made a firm decision about your chosen program and institution, you can begin to consider the application(s). The application process varies based on the institution and country, but typically every institution will have complete information on how to submit your application via its official website.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">In some instances, there may be submitting two applications for students from abroad. That means you have to submit two applications: one to be considered for admission into the university and the other to get a spot on the course. It should be stated clearly on the website of the university. If you are still unsure about the procedure, you can directly get in touch with the university you&rsquo;ve chosen.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">If you think you may require a visa for a student, be aware that in most instances, you will not be able to apply for one until you&rsquo;ve received an acceptance letter from the university you&rsquo;ve chosen. Each stage could take months, so be prepared to allow enough time.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_vtqc0eazt1cm\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">4. How long will study abroad programs run?</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">The amount of time you&rsquo;ll spend studying abroad will depend upon the type of program and education you&rsquo;re taking. In general, an undergraduate degree can take three years to complete full-time education (for instance that for the UK, the average duration for all subjects is three years, and within the US, the usual length is four years) and a graduate degree like master&rsquo;s or equivalent can require between one and two years. The doctoral (Ph.D.) degree will typically require three to four years.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Many universities allow studying abroad for a short period of duration. For example, students exchange programs permit you to take a semester or a year of study and a semester or only a few weeks. The information about these programs can be found on the website of the institution you&rsquo;re planning to attend and the institution you&rsquo;d like to receive hosting from.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_khi0v2pfdgge\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">5. When do I begin applying to be considered for study abroad opportunities?</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Examining your application as soon as possible is the best method to start. The sooner you are accepted into an institution, the quicker you plan your travels. To ensure you don&rsquo;t miss out, </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">write all of the necessary deadlines for applications (set by your selected university), and mark your calendar.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Deadlines for application will differ according to the school. However, for classes that start in the autumn (September/October), the application process typically opens from the beginning of the calendar year (January/February) up to the midpoint of the calendar year (June/July).</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_venjflryyxru\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">6. What are the entry requirements to participate in study abroad programs?</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">The requirements for admission vary significantly among universities and across nations, so be sure to review the details that your potential university provides before submitting any information.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">In general, applying for an undergraduate degree, you will need to prove that you&rsquo;ve finished your high school education at a level comparable to the requirements for grades (e.g., your GPA A-level marks or equivalent) for the degree you&rsquo;re applying to. However, if you hold an international degree and are not sure if it is acceptable, you need to get in touch with the admissions department at the university.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">For non-native English learners who want to study in English-speaking nations, you&rsquo;ll probably have to submit proof of your proficiency in English by taking an English-language exam like IELTS or TOEFL. In addition, similar tests might be required for students in different languages. For more details on language tests, see question number eight.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;\"><a name=\"_qxrnymiome7e\"></a><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">7. What information should I attach along with my application?</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">You might be required to submit additional documents as part of your application. The requirements will vary according to the institution and the country of study; however, international students are typically required to provide the following information:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; margin: 12.0pt 0in .0001pt .5in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">●<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Passport photos for identification</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">●<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\">Statement of Purpose/ Motivation Letter</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Roboto; mso-fareast-font-family: Roboto; mso-bidi-font-family: Roboto; color: #212529;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">●<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></s